ClassDecl.Name: Value
ClassDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>A type to store all values of reflectable types.</summary> </Document>

EnumItemDecl.Name: RawPtr
EnumItemDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>The value stored using a raw pointer.</summary> </Document>

EnumItemDecl.Name: SharedPtr
EnumItemDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>The value stored using a smart pointer.</summary> </Document>

EnumItemDecl.Name: BoxedValue
EnumItemDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>The value stored using a boxed value.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetValueType
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get how the value is stored.</summary> <returns>How the value is stored.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetRawPtr
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the stored raw pointer if possible.</summary> <returns>The stored raw pointer. Returns null if failed.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetSharedPtr
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the stored shared pointer if possible.</summary> <returns>The stored shared pointer. Returns null if failed.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetBoxedValue
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the stored text if possible.</summary> <returns>The stored text. Returns empty if failed.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: IsNull
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the real type of the stored object.</summary> <returns>The real type. Returns null if the value is null.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: From
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Store a raw pointer.</summary> <returns>The boxed value.</returns> <param name="value">The raw pointer to store.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: From
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Store a shared pointer.</summary> <returns>The boxed value.</returns> <param name="value">The shared pointer to store.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: From
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Store a text.</summary> <returns>The boxed value.</returns> <param name="value">The text to store.</param> <param name="type">The type that you expect to interpret the text.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: DeleteRawPtr
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Dispose the object is it is stored as a raw pointer.</summary> <returns>Returns true if the object is disposed. Returns false if the object cannot be disposed. An exception will be thrown if the reference counter is not 0.</returns> </Document>
